https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content:
In the HIP program, the first $2,500 of medical expenses for covered services are paid with a special savings account called a Personal Wellness and Responsibility (POWER) account. Every HIP member has their own POWER Account. The state pays most of the $2,500, and if you areÂ in HIP Plus or HIP State Plan Plus, you are responsible for paying a portion. Learn more about the POWER account Need help with some of the HIP terms? Try this guide
External Link
.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/POWER Up to HIP Plus
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: HIP Plus is the plan for the bestÂ value.Â HIP Plus provides health coverage for a low, predictable monthly cost. It alsoÂ includes more benefits like dental, vision, or chiropractic.Â With HIP Plus, youÂ do not have copaysÂ when you visit the doctor, fill a prescription or go to the hospital for an emergency. On average,Â HIP Plus members spend less moneyÂ on their health care expenses than HIP Basic members.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/What is Fast Track
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: Fast Track is a payment option that allows eligible Hoosiers to expedite the start of their coverage in the HIP Plus program. Fast Track allows you to make a $10 payment while your application is being processed. The $10 payment goes toward your first POWER account contribution.Â If you make a Fast Track payment and are eligible for HIP, your HIP Plus coverage will begin the first of the month in which you made your Fast Track payment.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/What happens if I dont make a Fast Track payment
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: What happens if I donât make a Fast Track payment?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: If you do not make a Fast Track payment, you may face a delay in the start of your coverage. For example, if you apply June 5 and receive a $10 Fast Track invoice on June 12, your HIP Plus coverage could be effective beginning June 1 â if you make your $10 payment in June. From the date the invoice is issued, you have 60 days to make either a Fast Track payment or your first POWER account contribution to be able to begin HIP Plus coverage . If you make your Fast Track payment or first POWER acco

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/How do I make a Fast Track payment
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: How do I make a Fast Track payment?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: You can make a Fast Track payment by credit card when you apply online or, after applying, while your application is being processed. Fast Track payments are made to the Managed Care Entity (MCE) or health plan, you select on your application to provide your HIP coverage (Anthem, Caresource, MDwise or MHS).Â After making the payment you may not change your MCE/health plan, so be sure you select the right one for you. For help making your selection, call 1-877-GET-HIP-9.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/Payments made with the online application
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: Payments made with the online application
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: Anyone who applies for Indiana Health Coverage Programs online will have the opportunity to make a Fast Track payment by credit card when completing the application. You must select a Managed Care Entity in order to make a payment at the time of application. If you make a Fast Track payment and are determined to be eligible for HIP then your HIP Plus coverage will begin the first of the month that you submitted your application.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/Payments made while your application is being processed
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: Payments made while your application is being processed
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: If you do not apply online, or choose not to make a Fast Track payment when you apply, you will still have the opportunity to make a Fast Track payment while your application is being processed. You will receive a Fast Track invoice from the Managed Care Entity (MCE) you selected to provide your health coverage. If you did not select an MCE you will be automatically assigned to one. If you pay the Fast Track invoice and are determined to be eligible for HIP then your HIP Plus coverage will begin

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/What if my POWER account contribution is not 10
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: What if my POWER account contribution is not $10?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: If you are found eligible for HIP and you make your $10 Fast Track payment, this payment will be applied toward your POWER account contribution(s). Your monthly POWER Account contribution will be based on your income. This may be more or less than $10 per month. If your POWER account contribution amount is less than $10 per month, your $10 payment will be applied to your initial coverage month with the remaining amount applied to future months. For example if your POWER account contribution is $

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/What if I am not eligible for HIP
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: What if I am not eligible for HIP?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: You are offered the opportunity to make a Fast Track payment before you have been found eligible for HIP. If you are not found eligible for HIP and you have made a Fast Track payment, this payment will be refunded to you by the MCE (Anthem, Caresource, MDwise or MHS) that took the payment.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/Do I have to make a Fast Track payment
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: Do I have to make a Fast Track payment?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: While making a Fast Track payment can help ensure you get enrolled in HIP Plus as quickly as possible, you are NOT required to make a Fast Track payment. From the date you receive your initial Fast Track invoice you will have 60 days to make a payment to start your HIP Plus coverage. You can pay either the $10 Fast Track payment or your POWER account contribution amount. If you do not make your contribution or Fast Track payment within 60 days and your income is less than the federal poverty lev

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/Can someone make my Fast Track payment for me
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: Can someone make my Fast Track payment for me?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: Yes. You may have someone make your Fast Track payment on your behalf. However, as is the policy with all HIP payments, once a payment is made (whether you or someone else pays it), you will not be able to change your MCE/health plan. If a health care provider makes a Fast Track payment for you, the provider should ask you to complete a form that gives them permission to make this payment (PDF)External Link. If you need help picking the right health plan for you, call 1-877-GET-HIP-9.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/Once I make a Fast Track payment, can I change my MCEhealth plan
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: Once I make a Fast Track payment, can I change my MCE/health plan?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: No. Once you pay your Fast Track invoice you may not change your MCE/health plan. You may change your health plan selection before paying your Fast Track invoice by calling 1-877-GET-HIP-9. You can pay your Fast Track invoice or POWER account contribution to your new health plan and your coverage will start the month in which your payment is received and processed. Only make a payment to the health plan that you want to be your HIP coverage provider. You will not have the opportunity to change y

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_text: What if I didnât get a Fast Track invoice?
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: Only those individuals who may be eligible for HIP will receive a Fast Track invoice. If you applied and did not receive a Fast Track invoice it could be because you are eligible for another coverage program â such as if you indicated that you are pregnant, disabled, a former foster care child or on Medicare when you applied. https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/HIP State Plan Plus Costs
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: HIP State Plan Plus members pay an affordable monthly contribution, based on their income. If you do not pay your monthly contribution on time, you will be moved to HIP State Plan Basic.

https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.semantic_path: https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indiana Plan/HIP State Plan Basic Costs
https://www.mhsindiana.com//Healthy Indi.element_content: HIP Basic members do not have a simple, predictable monthly contribution. Instead you are responsible for paying for copayments at the time of service. Because of this, the HIP Basic plan could be more expensive than paying a monthly contribution to stay in HIP State Plan Plus.

For most other health problems, your MHS doctor knows about your health and is the best person to call. If you are not sure whether you should go to the ER, please call your MHSÂ doctor or the MHS 24-Hour Nurse Advice line atÂ 1-877-647-4848. For more information about when to go to the ER, check out theÂ Emergency Room: Know When to Go flyer on our Brochures and Guides page.

MHSÂ allows for some self-referral specialist visits. A self-referral means that you do not have to get a referral from your doctor.
